[2026/05/08 10:55:21] [DEBUG] isgsa.llm: prompt content: {'Instructions': 'You are an expert recommender system researcher conducting a code review for an important experiment. You are provided the research task, the code implementation and the execution output. You must score the code using the following requirements: \n1. Use LensKit 0.14.4 APIs only, and ensure all code is compatible with that exact version.\n2. Load the raw files from the working directory using these filenames exactly: u.data, VideoGames.csv, UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat.\n3. Parse each dataset correctly: MovieLens100K from tab-separated user-item-rating-timestamp format, Amazon Video Games from CSV format, and Last.FM from the tagged-artists DAT file with its documented delimiter/schema.\n4. Convert all datasets to implicit-feedback interaction data before splitting and training.\n5. For MovieLens100K and Amazon Video Games, keep only interactions with rating > 3 before implicit conversion; discard all other ratings.\n6. For Last.FM, treat observed user-artist events in UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat as implicit interactions.\n7. Apply 5-core filtering to every dataset before splitting, iterating until all remaining users and items each have at least 5 interactions.\n8. Remove duplicate user-item pairs after implicit conversion so each interaction is binary and counted once.\n9. Generate exactly 5 distinct random seeds for the data splits and record them in the output for reproducibility.\n10. For each dataset and each seed, perform a user-based random 80/20 holdout split using the seed, so each user’s interactions are partitioned into train/test with approximately 80% train and 20% test.\n11. Exclude users that cannot support a valid 80/20 split after preprocessing (e.g., fewer than 2 interactions), and report any exclusions.\n12. Train exactly these three algorithms on each train split: ALS, ItemKNN, and Pop.\n13. Use standard/default LensKit hyperparameters for ALS, ItemKNN, and Pop unless a parameter is required to make the model train on implicit data.\n14. Configure ALS appropriately for implicit-feedback training if LensKit 0.14.4 requires an explicit implicit-feedback setting.\n15. Generate top-N recommendations for evaluation from each trained model for all eligible test users.\n16. Exclude from recommendation candidates any items the user has already seen in the corresponding training split.\n17. Evaluate recommendation quality using nDCG@1, nDCG@5, nDCG@10 and Precision@1, Precision@5, Precision@10.\n18. Compute metrics against the held-out implicit test items per user, then aggregate to dataset-level means for each algorithm-seed combination.\n19. Save per-user metrics or sufficient intermediate outputs to enable statistical analysis across seeds and algorithms.\n20. Produce a results table containing dataset, algorithm, seed, nDCG@1/5/10, and Precision@1/5/10.\n21. Quantify seed sensitivity by summarizing metric variation across the 5 seeds for each dataset-algorithm pair (at minimum mean, standard deviation, and range).\n22. Conduct a short statistical analysis across seeds, such as confidence intervals or repeated-measures comparisons, and clearly state the unit of analysis and test used.\n23. Ensure the analysis distinguishes seed effects from algorithm and dataset effects; do not pool incompatible conditions without labeling them.\n24. Handle datasets robustly: missing values, malformed rows, and delimiter/header differences must not crash the experiment.\n25. Make the full pipeline reproducible by fixing and logging all random seeds used in splitting and any model-training randomness.\n26. Structure the code to run all 3 datasets × 3 algorithms × 5 seeds automatically and without manual intervention.\n27. Output a concise experimental summary describing preprocessing counts, number of users/items/interactions after 5-core filtering, and any dropped records/users.\n28. Verify that evaluation only includes users present in both train and test for a given split.\n29. Avoid data leakage by applying all preprocessing that depends only on raw interactions before splitting, and by fitting models only on each training partition.\n30. Save final results and summary statistics to disk in a machine-readable format (e.g., CSV).\n. Each requirement can either be fullfilled or not fulfilled. The score is the percentage of requirements that are fulfilled, e.g. if 7 out of 10 requirements are fulfilled, the score is 70. Additionally, you provide clear and constructive feedback how to improve the code implementation based on the requirements.', 'Research Task': " You are an expert recommender systems research assistant who is looking to help the user with their requests.\nThe user has some idea and you want to conduct creative experiments to gain scientific insights.\nYour aim is to run experiments to gather sufficient results to report back to the user.\nThe idea is:\n\nI'd like to run an experiment to quantify how much data split random seeds affect recommender system accuracy. Please use LensKit 0.14.4 to test three algorithms: ALS, ItemKNN, and Pop. Run this on the following three datasets with implicit feedback: MovieLens100K, Amazon Video Games, Last.FM. The raw files are stored in your working directory with the filenames u.data, VideoGames.csv, UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat. First, preprocess all datasets with 5-core filtering. For the Amazon and MovieLens datasets, please also convert any ratings greater than 3 to implicit interactions. Here's the main experimental procedure: Generate 5 different random seeds for data splitting. For each algorithm, dataset, and seed, please do a user-based 80/20 holdout split. Train all models using standard hyperparameters. For the analysis, I need you to measure nDCG@k and Precision@k for k=1, 5, 10 and conduct a short statistical analysis.", 'Implementation': '```python\nimport os\nworking_dir = os.path.join(os.getcwd(), \'working\')\nos.makedirs(working_dir, exist_ok=True)\n\nimport warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings(\'ignore\')\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nfrom scipy.stats import ttest_rel\n\nfrom lenskit.algorithms import Recommender\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.basic import Popular\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.als import ImplicitMF\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.item_knn import ItemItem\nfrom lenskit import batch\n\nSEEDS = [1, 7, 21, 42, 84]\nKS = [1, 5, 10]\n\nexperiment_data = {\n    \'ml100k\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': []},\n    \'amazon_videogames\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': []},\n    \'lastfm\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': []},\n}\n\n\ndef k_core_filter(df, user_col=\'user\', item_col=\'item\', min_uc=5, min_ic=5):\n    df = df[[user_col, item_col]].drop_duplicates().copy()\n    while True:\n        uc = df[user_col].value_counts()\n        ic = df[item_col].value_counts()\n        keep_u = uc[uc >= min_uc].index\n        keep_i = ic[ic >= min_ic].index\n        new_df = df[df[user_col].isin(keep_u) & df[item_col].isin(keep_i)]\n        if len(new_df) == len(df):\n            break\n        df = new_df\n    return df.reset_index(drop=True)\n\n\ndef load_ml100k(path=\'u.data\'):\n    df = pd.read_csv(path, sep=\'\\t\', header=None, names=[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\', \'timestamp\'])\n    df = df[df[\'rating\'] > 3][[\'user\', \'item\']].copy()\n    return k_core_filter(df)\n\n\ndef load_amazon(path=\'VideoGames.csv\'):\n    cols = [\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\', \'timestamp\']\n    df = pd.read_csv(path, header=None, names=cols)\n    df = df[df[\'rating\'] > 3][[\'user\', \'item\']].copy()\n    return k_core_filter(df)\n\n\ndef load_lastfm(path=\'UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat\'):\n    df = pd.read_csv(path, sep=\'\\t\')\n    user_col = \'userID\' if \'userID\' in df.columns else df.columns[0]\n    item_col = \'artistID\' if \'artistID\' in df.columns else df.columns[1]\n    df = df[[user_col, item_col]].rename(columns={user_col: \'user\', item_col: \'item\'})\n    return k_core_filter(df)\n\n\ndef user_holdout_split(df, test_ratio=0.2, seed=42):\n    rng = np.random.default_rng(seed)\n    train_parts, test_parts = [], []\n    for _, g in df.groupby(\'user\', sort=False):\n        n = len(g)\n        n_test = max(1, int(np.ceil(n * test_ratio)))\n        idx = np.arange(n)\n        rng.shuffle(idx)\n        test_idx = idx[:n_test]\n        mask = np.zeros(n, dtype=bool)\n        mask[test_idx] = True\n        test_parts.append(g.iloc[mask])\n        train_parts.append(g.iloc[~mask])\n    train = pd.concat(train_parts, ignore_index=True)\n    test = pd.concat(test_parts, ignore_index=True)\n    return train, test\n\n\ndef get_algorithms():\n    return {\n        \'ALS\': Recommender.adapt(ImplicitMF(features=50, iterations=15, reg=0.01, weight=40)),\n        \'ItemKNN\': Recommender.adapt(ItemItem(30, feedback=\'implicit\')),\n        \'Pop\': Recommender.adapt(Popular()),\n    }\n\n\ndef precision_at_k(recs, truth, k):\n    if len(recs) == 0:\n        return 0.0\n    recs_k = recs[:k]\n    return sum(1 for x in recs_k if x in truth) / k\n\n\ndef ndcg_at_k(recs, truth, k):\n    recs_k = recs[:k]\n    dcg = 0.0\n    for i, item in enumerate(recs_k, start=1):\n        if item in truth:\n            dcg += 1.0 / np.log2(i + 1)\n    ideal_hits = min(len(truth), k)\n    if ideal_hits == 0:\n        return 0.0\n    idcg = sum(1.0 / np.log2(i + 1) for i in range(1, ideal_hits + 1))\n    return dcg / idcg\n\n\ndef evaluate_model(model, train, test, algo_name, dataset_name, seed):\n    model.fit(train)\n    users = test[\'user\'].unique()\n    truth = test.groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].apply(set).to_dict()\n    recs = batch.recommend(model, users, 10)\n    if recs is None or len(recs) == 0:\n        recs = pd.DataFrame(columns=[\'user\', \'item\', \'rank\', \'score\'])\n    user_recs = recs.groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].apply(list).to_dict()\n\n    rows = []\n    for u in users:\n        r = user_recs.get(u, [])\n        t = truth.get(u, set())\n        row = {\'dataset\': dataset_name, \'algorithm\': algo_name, \'seed\': seed, \'user\': u}\n        for k in KS:\n            row[f\'P@{k}\'] = precision_at_k(r, t, k)\n            row[f\'nDCG@{k}\'] = ndcg_at_k(r, t, k)\n        rows.append(row)\n    udf = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n    summary = udf[[f\'P@{k}\' for k in KS] + [f\'nDCG@{k}\' for k in KS]].mean().to_dict()\n    print(f\'Seed {seed} | {dataset_name} | {algo_name} | validation_loss = {1 - summary["nDCG@10"]:.4f}\')\n    print({k: round(v, 4) for k, v in summary.items()})\n    experiment_data[dataset_name][\'metrics\'][\'val\'].append({\'seed\': seed, \'algorithm\': algo_name, **summary})\n    experiment_data[dataset_name][\'predictions\'].append(recs[[\'user\', \'item\']].to_dict(\'records\'))\n    experiment_data[dataset_name][\'ground_truth\'].append(test[[\'user\', \'item\']].to_dict(\'records\'))\n    experiment_data[dataset_name][\'losses\'][\'val\'].append({\'seed\': seed, \'algorithm\': algo_name, \'validation_loss\': 1 - summary[\'nDCG@10\']})\n    return udf, recs\n\n\ndef plot_metric_boxplots(results_df, dataset_name):\n    for metric in [\'nDCG@10\', \'P@10\']:\n        pivot = results_df.pivot_table(index=\'seed\', columns=\'algorithm\', values=metric, aggfunc=\'mean\')\n        arrs = [pivot[c].dropna().values for c in pivot.columns]\n        plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))\n        plt.boxplot(arrs, labels=list(pivot.columns))\n        plt.ylabel(metric)\n        plt.title(f\'{dataset_name}: {metric} over split seeds\')\n        plt.tight_layout()\n        fig_path = os.path.join(working_dir, f\'{dataset_name}_{metric.replace("@", "at")}_boxplot.png\')\n        plt.savefig(fig_path, dpi=150)\n        plt.close()\n        np.save(os.path.join(working_dir, f\'{dataset_name}_{metric.replace("@", "at")}_boxplot_data.npy\'), {c: pivot[c].dropna().values for c in pivot.columns}, allow_pickle=True)\n\n\ndatasets = {\n    \'ml100k\': load_ml100k(\'u.data\'),\n    \'amazon_videogames\': load_amazon(\'VideoGames.csv\'),\n    \'lastfm\': load_lastfm(\'UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat\'),\n}\n\nall_user_metrics = []\nall_seed_metrics = []\n\nfor dname, df in datasets.items():\n    print(f\'Loaded {dname}: {len(df):,} interactions, {df.user.nunique():,} users, {df.item.nunique():,} items\')\n    for seed in SEEDS:\n        train, test = user_holdout_split(df, test_ratio=0.2, seed=seed)\n        experiment_data[dname][\'metrics\'][\'train\'].append({\'seed\': seed, \'n_train\': len(train), \'n_test\': len(test)})\n        algos = get_algorithms()\n        for aname, algo in algos.items():\n            udf, recs = evaluate_model(algo, train, test, aname, dname, seed)\n            all_user_metrics.append(udf)\n            seed_summary = udf.drop(columns=[\'user\']).mean(numeric_only=True).to_dict()\n            seed_summary.update({\'dataset\': dname, \'algorithm\': aname, \'seed\': seed})\n            all_seed_metrics.append(seed_summary)\n\nuser_metrics_df = pd.concat(all_user_metrics, ignore_index=True)\nseed_metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(all_seed_metrics)\n\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, \'experiment_data.npy\'), experiment_data, allow_pickle=True)\nnp.savez_compressed(os.path.join(working_dir, \'seed_metrics.npz\'), data=seed_metrics_df.to_records(index=False))\nnp.savez_compressed(os.path.join(working_dir, \'user_metrics.npz\'), data=user_metrics_df.to_records(index=False))\n\nprint(\'\\nAggregate results over seeds (mean ± std):\')\nagg = seed_metrics_df.groupby([\'dataset\', \'algorithm\'])[[f\'P@{k}\' for k in KS] + [f\'nDCG@{k}\' for k in KS]].agg([\'mean\', \'std\'])\nprint(agg.round(4))\n\nprint(\'\\nPaired t-tests on nDCG@10 versus Pop across seeds:\')\nfor dname in datasets:\n    sub = seed_metrics_df[seed_metrics_df[\'dataset\'] == dname]\n    pop = sub[sub[\'algorithm\'] == \'Pop\'].sort_values(\'seed\')[\'nDCG@10\'].values\n    for algo in [\'ALS\', \'ItemKNN\']:\n        vals = sub[sub[\'algorithm\'] == algo].sort_values(\'seed\')[\'nDCG@10\'].values\n        if len(vals) == len(pop) == len(SEEDS):\n            t, p = ttest_rel(vals, pop)\n            print(f\'{dname} | {algo} vs Pop: t={t:.4f}, p={p:.4f}\')\n\nfor dname in datasets:\n    plot_metric_boxplots(seed_metrics_df[seed_metrics_df[\'dataset\'] == dname], dname)\n\nseed_metrics_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, \'seed_metrics.csv\'), index=False)\nuser_metrics_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, \'user_metrics.csv\'), index=False)\nprint(f\'Artifacts saved to: {working_dir}\')\n```', 'Execution output': "```\nLoaded ml100k: 54,413 interactions, 938 users, 1,008 items\nNumba is using threading layer omp - consider TBB\nfound 1 potential runtime problems - see https://boi.st/lkpy-perf\nSeed 1 | ml100k | ALS | validation_loss = 0.7981\n{'P@1': 0.193, 'P@5': 0.1714, 'P@10': 0.1471, 'nDCG@1': 0.193, 'nDCG@5': 0.1903, 'nDCG@10': 0.2019}\nSeed 1 | ml100k | ItemKNN | validation_loss = 0.7542\n{'P@1': 0.2868, 'P@5': 0.2194, 'P@10': 0.1758, 'nDCG@1': 0.2868, 'nDCG@5': 0.2507, 'nDCG@10': 0.2458}\nSeed 1 | ml100k | Pop | validation_loss = 0.8479\n{'P@1': 0.2036, 'P@5': 0.1388, 'P@10': 0.1188, 'nDCG@1': 0.2036, 'nDCG@5': 0.1565, 'nDCG@10': 0.1521}\nSeed 7 | ml100k | ALS | validation_loss = 0.7865\n{'P@1': 0.2249, 'P@5': 0.1757, 'P@10': 0.1517, 'nDCG@1': 0.2249, 'nDCG@5': 0.2016, 'nDCG@10': 0.2135}\nSeed 7 | ml100k | ItemKNN | validation_loss = 0.7455\n{'P@1': 0.323, 'P@5': 0.2299, 'P@10': 0.1785, 'nDCG@1': 0.323, 'nDCG@5': 0.265, 'nDCG@10': 0.2545}\nSeed 7 | ml100k | Pop | validation_loss = 0.8415\n{'P@1': 0.21, 'P@5': 0.1499, 'P@10': 0.1225, 'nDCG@1': 0.21, 'nDCG@5': 0.1663, 'nDCG@10': 0.1585}\nSeed 21 | ml100k | ALS | validation_loss = 0.7952\n{'P@1': 0.2068, 'P@5': 0.1738,