[2026/05/08 11:36:32] [DEBUG] isgsa.llm: prompt content: {'Introduction': 'You are an experienced recommender systems researcher. Your previous code for research experiment had a bug, so based on the information below, you should revise it in order to fix this bug. Your response should be an implementation outline in natural language, followed by a single markdown code block which implements the bugfix/solution.', 'Research task': " You are an expert recommender systems research assistant who is looking to help the user with their requests.\nThe user has some idea and you want to conduct creative experiments to gain scientific insights.\nYour aim is to run experiments to gather sufficient results to report back to the user.\nThe idea is:\n\nI'd like to run an experiment to quantify how much data split random seeds affect recommender system accuracy. Please use LensKit 0.14.4 to test three algorithms: ALS, ItemKNN, and Pop. Run this on the following three datasets with implicit feedback: MovieLens100K, Amazon Video Games, Last.FM. The raw files are stored in your working directory with the filenames u.data, VideoGames.csv, UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat. First, preprocess all datasets with 5-core filtering. For the Amazon and MovieLens datasets, please also convert any ratings greater than 3 to implicit interactions. Here's the main experimental procedure: Generate 5 different random seeds for data splitting. For each algorithm, dataset, and seed, please do a user-based 80/20 holdout split. Train all models using standard hyperparameters. For the analysis, I need you to measure nDCG@k and Precision@k for k=1, 5, 10 and conduct a short statistical analysis.", 'Previous (buggy) implementation': '```python\nimport os\nworking_dir = os.path.join(os.getcwd(), \'working\')\nos.makedirs(working_dir, exist_ok=True)\n\nimport warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings(\'ignore\')\n\nimport inspect\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom scipy.stats import ttest_rel, t\n\nfrom lenskit import batch\nfrom lenskit.algorithms import Recommender\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.basic import Popular\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.als import ImplicitMF\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.item_knn import ItemItem\n\nSEEDS = [1, 7, 21, 42, 84]\nKS = [1, 5, 10]\n\nexperiment_data = {\n    \'ml100k\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': [], \'preprocess\': []},\n    \'amazon_videogames\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': [], \'preprocess\': []},\n    \'lastfm\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': [], \'preprocess\': []},\n}\n\n\ndef robust_read_csv(path, **kwargs):\n    kwargs = dict(kwargs)\n    kwargs.setdefault(\'on_bad_lines\', \'skip\')\n    try:\n        return pd.read_csv(path, **kwargs)\n    except TypeError:\n        kwargs.pop(\'on_bad_lines\', None)\n        return pd.read_csv(path, error_bad_lines=False, warn_bad_lines=False, **kwargs)\n\n\ndef standardize_pairs(df, user_col, item_col):\n    out = df[[user_col, item_col]].copy()\n    out.columns = [\'user\', \'item\']\n    out[\'user\'] = out[\'user\'].astype(str).str.strip()\n    out[\'item\'] = out[\'item\'].astype(str).str.strip()\n    out = out.replace({\'\': np.nan, \'nan\': np.nan, \'None\': np.nan})\n    out = out.dropna().drop_duplicates().reset_index(drop=True)\n    return out\n\n\ndef k_core_filter(df, user_col=\'user\', item_col=\'item\', min_uc=5, min_ic=5):\n    cur = df[[user_col, item_col]].drop_duplicates().copy()\n    while True:\n        uc = cur[user_col].value_counts()\n        ic = cur[item_col].value_counts()\n        keep_u = set(uc[uc >= min_uc].index)\n        keep_i = set(ic[ic >= min_ic].index)\n        new = cur[cur[user_col].isin(keep_u) & cur[item_col].isin(keep_i)].copy()\n        if len(new) == len(cur):\n            break\n        cur = new\n    return cur.reset_index(drop=True)\n\n\ndef load_ml100k(path=\'u.data\'):\n    raw = robust_read_csv(path, sep=\'\\t\', header=None, names=[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\', \'timestamp\'])\n    raw[\'rating\'] = pd.to_numeric(raw[\'rating\'], errors=\'coerce\')\n    raw = raw.dropna(subset=[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\'])\n    pre_n = len(raw)\n    raw = raw[raw[\'rating\'] > 3]\n    pairs = standardize_pairs(raw, \'user\', \'item\')\n    filtered = k_core_filter(pairs)\n    summary = {\n        \'raw_rows\': int(pre_n), \'after_threshold\': int(len(pairs)), \'after_kcore\': int(len(filtered)),\n        \'users\': int(filtered.user.nunique()), \'items\': int(filtered.item.nunique()), \'dropped_rows\': int(pre_n - len(filtered))\n    }\n    return filtered, summary\n\n\ndef load_amazon(path=\'VideoGames.csv\'):\n    raw = robust_read_csv(path, header=None)\n    if raw.shape[1] < 3:\n        raise ValueError(\'VideoGames.csv must have at least 3 columns\')\n    raw = raw.iloc[:, :4].copy()\n    cols = [\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\', \'timestamp\'][:raw.shape[1]]\n    raw.columns = cols\n    raw[\'rating\'] = pd.to_numeric(raw[\'rating\'], errors=\'coerce\')\n    raw = raw.dropna(subset=[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\'])\n    pre_n = len(raw)\n    raw = raw[raw[\'rating\'] > 3]\n    pairs = standardize_pairs(raw, \'user\', \'item\')\n    filtered = k_core_filter(pairs)\n    summary = {\n        \'raw_rows\': int(pre_n), \'after_threshold\': int(len(pairs)), \'after_kcore\': int(len(filtered)),\n        \'users\': int(filtered.user.nunique()), \'items\': int(filtered.item.nunique()), \'dropped_rows\': int(pre_n - len(filtered))\n    }\n    return filtered, summary\n\n\ndef load_lastfm(path=\'UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat\'):\n    raw = robust_read_csv(path, sep=\'\\t\')\n    cols = {c.lower(): c for c in raw.columns}\n    user_col = cols[\'userid\'] if \'userid\' in cols else raw.columns[0]\n    item_col = cols[\'artistid\'] if \'artistid\' in cols else raw.columns[1]\n    raw = raw.dropna(subset=[user_col, item_col])\n    pre_n = len(raw)\n    pairs = standardize_pairs(raw, user_col, item_col)\n    filtered = k_core_filter(pairs)\n    summary = {\n        \'raw_rows\': int(pre_n), \'after_threshold\': int(len(pairs)), \'after_kcore\': int(len(filtered)),\n        \'users\': int(filtered.user.nunique()), \'items\': int(filtered.item.nunique()), \'dropped_rows\': int(pre_n - len(filtered))\n    }\n    return filtered, summary\n\n\ndef user_holdout_split(df, test_ratio=0.2, seed=42):\n    rng = np.random.default_rng(seed)\n    user_sizes = df.groupby(\'user\').size()\n    valid_users = user_sizes[user_sizes >= 2].index\n    excluded_users = int((user_sizes < 2).sum())\n    df = df[df[\'user\'].isin(valid_users)].copy()\n    train_parts, test_parts = [], []\n    for _, g in df.groupby(\'user\', sort=False):\n        n = len(g)\n        n_test = max(1, int(np.floor(n * test_ratio)))\n        if n_test >= n:\n            n_test = n - 1\n        idx = np.arange(n)\n        rng.shuffle(idx)\n        test_idx = idx[:n_test]\n        mask = np.zeros(n, dtype=bool)\n        mask[test_idx] = True\n        train_parts.append(g.iloc[~mask])\n        test_parts.append(g.iloc[mask])\n    train = pd.concat(train_parts, ignore_index=True)\n    test = pd.concat(test_parts, ignore_index=True)\n    return train, test, excluded_users\n\n\ndef make_algo(name, seed):\n    if name == \'Pop\':\n        return Recommender.adapt(Popular())\n    if name == \'ALS\':\n        params = inspect.signature(ImplicitMF).parameters\n        kwargs = {}\n        if \'random_state\' in params:\n            kwargs[\'random_state\'] = seed\n        return Recommender.adapt(ImplicitMF(**kwargs))\n    if name == \'ItemKNN\':\n        params = inspect.signature(ItemItem).parameters\n        kwargs = {}\n        if \'feedback\' in params:\n            kwargs[\'feedback\'] = \'implicit\'\n        return Recommender.adapt(ItemItem(**kwargs))\n    raise ValueError(name)\n\n\ndef precision_at_k(recs, truth, k):\n    recs = recs[:k]\n    return sum(1 for x in recs if x in truth) / k if k else 0.0\n\n\ndef ndcg_at_k(recs, truth, k):\n    recs = recs[:k]\n    dcg = sum((1.0 / np.log2(i + 2)) for i, x in enumerate(recs) if x in truth)\n    ideal = min(len(truth), k)\n    if ideal == 0:\n        return 0.0\n    idcg = sum(1.0 / np.log2(i + 2) for i in range(ideal))\n    return dcg / idcg\n\n\ndef evaluate_model(model, train, test, algo_name, dataset_name, seed):\n    model.fit(train)\n    users = np.array(sorted(test[\'user\'].unique()))\n    truth = test.groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].apply(set).to_dict()\n    seen = train.groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].apply(set).to_dict()\n    recs = batch.recommend(model, users, 50)\n    if recs is None or len(recs) == 0:\n        recs = pd.DataFrame(columns=[\'user\', \'item\', \'rank\', \'score\'])\n    recs = recs[~recs.apply(lambda r: r[\'item\'] in seen.get(r[\'user\'], set()), axis=1)].copy()\n    recs[\'rank2\'] = recs.groupby(\'user\').cumcount() + 1\n    recs = recs[recs[\'rank2\'] <= 10].drop(columns=[\'rank2\'])\n    user_recs = recs.groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].apply(list).to_dict()\n\n    rows = []\n    for u in users:\n        r = user_recs.get(u, [])\n        tset = truth.get(u, set())\n        row = {\'dataset\': dataset_name, \'algorithm\': algo_name, \'seed\': seed, \'user\': u}\n        for k in KS:\n            row[f\'P@{k}\'] = precision_at_k(r, tset, k)\n            row[f\'nDCG@{k}\'] = ndcg_at_k(r, tset, k)\n        rows.append(row)\n    udf = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n    summary = {\'dataset\': dataset_name, \'algorithm\': algo_name, \'seed\': seed}\n    for c in [f\'P@{k}\' for k in KS] + [f\'nDCG@{k}\' for k in KS]:\n        summary[c] = float(udf[c].mean())\n    val_loss = 1.0 - summary[\'nDCG@10\']\n    print(f\'Seed {seed} | {dataset_name} | {algo_name} | validation_loss = {val_loss:.4f}\')\n    print({k: round(v, 4) for k, v in summary.items() if k not in [\'dataset\', \'algorithm\', \'seed\']})\n\n    experiment_data[dataset_name][\'metrics\'][\'val\'].append(summary)\n    experiment_data[dataset_name][\'losses\'][\'val\'].append({\'seed\': seed, \'algorithm\': algo_name, \'validation_loss\': val_loss})\n    experiment_data[dataset_name][\'predictions\'].append(recs[[\'user\', \'item\']].to_dict(\'records\'))\n    experiment_data[dataset_name][\'ground_truth\'].append(test[[\'user\', \'item\']].to_dict(\'records\'))\n    return udf, summary\n\n\ndatasets = {}\nloaders = {\n    \'ml100k\': load_ml100k,\n    \'amazon_videogames\': load_amazon,\n    \'lastfm\': load_lastfm,\n}\nfiles = {\n    \'ml100k\': \'u.data\',\n    \'amazon_videogames\': \'VideoGames.csv\',\n    \'lastfm\': \'UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat\',\n}\n\nfor dname in [\'ml100k\', \'amazon_videogames\', \'lastfm\']:\n    df, summary = loaders[dname](files[dname])\n    datasets[dname] = df\n    experiment_data[dname][\'preprocess\'].append(summary)\n    print(f"Loaded {dname}: {summary}")\n\nall_user_metrics, all_seed_metrics, preprocess_rows = [], [], []\nfor dname, df in datasets.items():\n    preprocess_rows.append({\'dataset\': dname, **experiment_data[dname][\'preprocess\'][0]})\n    for seed in SEEDS:\n        train, test, excluded_users = user_holdout_split(df, test_ratio=0.2, seed=seed)\n        split_info = {\'seed\': seed, \'n_train\': len(train), \'n_test\': len(test), \'excluded_users_lt2\': excluded_users}\n        experiment_data[dname][\'metrics\'][\'train\'].append(split_info)\n        print(f"Split {dname} seed={seed}: train={len(train)}, test={len(test)}, excluded_users_lt2={excluded_users}")\n        for aname in [\'ALS\', \'ItemKNN\', \'Pop\']:\n            algo = make_algo(aname, seed)\n            udf, summary = evaluate_model(algo, train, test, aname, dname, seed)\n            all_user_metrics.append(udf)\n            all_seed_metrics.append(summary)\n\nuser_metrics_df = pd.concat(all_user_metrics, ignore_index=True)\nseed_metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(all_seed_metrics)\npreprocess_df = pd.DataFrame(preprocess_rows)\n\nprint(\'\\nAggregate results over seeds (mean/std/min/max):\')\nagg = seed_metrics_df.groupby([\'dataset\', \'algorithm\'])[[f\'P@{k}\' for k in KS] + [f\'nDCG@{k}\' for k in KS]].agg([\'mean\', \'std\', \'min\', \'max\'])\nprint(agg.round(4))\n\nprint(\'\\nPaired t-tests and 95% CI for nDCG@10 differences across seeds:\')\nstats_rows = []\nfor dname in datasets:\n    sub = seed_metrics_df[seed_metrics_df[\'dataset\'] == dname]\n    for a1, a2 in [(\'ALS\', \'Pop\'), (\'ItemKNN\', \'Pop\'), (\'ALS\', \'ItemKNN\')]:\n        x = sub[sub[\'algorithm\'] == a1].sort_values(\'seed\')[\'nDCG@10\'].values\n        y = sub[sub[\'algorithm\'] == a2].sort_values(\'seed\')[\'nDCG@10\'].values\n        if len(x) == len(y) == len(SEEDS):\n            diff = x - y\n            mean_diff = float(diff.mean())\n            sd = float(diff.std(ddof=1)) if len(diff) > 1 else 0.0\n            se = sd / np.sqrt(len(diff)) if len(diff) > 1 else 0.0\n            crit = t.ppf(0.975, df=len(diff)-1) if len(diff) > 1 else np.nan\n            ci_low = mean_diff - crit * se if len(diff) > 1 else np.nan\n            ci_high = mean_diff + crit * se if len(diff) > 1 else np.nan\n            tt, pv = ttest_rel(x, y)\n            row = {\'dataset\': dname, \'compare\': f\'{a1} - {a2}\', \'mean_diff_nDCG@10\': mean_diff, \'t_stat\': float(tt), \'p_value\': float(pv), \'ci95_low\': ci_low, \'ci95_high\': ci_high}\n            stats_rows.append(row)\n            print(row)\nstats_df = pd.DataFrame(stats_rows)\n\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, \'experiment_data.npy\'), experiment_data, allow_pickle=True)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, \'preprocess_summary.npy\'), preprocess_df.to_dict(\'records\'), allow_pickle=True)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, \'seed_metrics_array.npy\'), seed_metrics_df.to_dict(\'records\'), allow_pickle=True)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, \'user_metrics_array.npy\'), user_metrics_df.to_dict(\'records\'), allow_pickle=True)\nnp.savez_compressed(os.path.join(working_dir, \'results_tables.npz\'),\n                    seed_metrics=seed_metrics_df.to_records(index=False),\n                    user_metrics=user_metrics_df.to_records(index=False),\n                    preprocess=preprocess_df.to_records(index=False),\n                    stats=stats_df.to_records(index=False))\n\npreprocess_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, \'preprocess_summary.csv\'), index=False)\nseed_metrics_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, \'seed_metrics.csv\'), index=False)\nuser_metrics_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, \'user_metrics.csv\'), index=False)\nstats_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, \'stats_summary.csv\'), index=False)\nprint(f\'Artifacts saved to: {working_dir}\')\n```', 'Execution output': '```\nLoaded ml100k: {\'raw_rows\': 100000, \'after_threshold\': 55375, \'after_kcore\': 54413, \'users\': 938, \'items\': 1008, \'dropped_rows\': 45587}\nLoaded amazon_videogames: {\'raw_rows\': 231780, \'after_threshold\': 231780, \'after_kcore\': 231780, \'users\': 24303, \'items\': 10672, \'dropped_rows\': 0}\nLoaded lastfm: {\'raw_rows\': 186479, \'after_threshold\': 71064, \'after_kcore\': 52551, \'users\': 1090, \'items\': 3646, \'dropped_rows\': 133928}\nSplit ml100k seed=1: train=43899, test=10514, excluded_users_lt2=0\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File "C:\\Users\\Robin\\Documents\\GitHub\\AutoRecLabTeam5\\treesearch\\interpreter.py", line 147, in _run_session\n    exec(compile(code, self.agent_file_name, "exec"), global_scope)\n  File "runfile.py", line 235, in <module>\n    algo = make_algo(aname, seed)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File "runfile.py", line 146, in make_algo\n    return Recommender.adapt(ImplicitMF(**kwargs))\n                             ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nTypeError: ImplicitMF.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: \'features\'\nExecution time: a second seconds (time limit is an hour).\n```', 'Bug An