[2026/05/08 13:29:37] [DEBUG] isgsa.llm: prompt content: {'Introduction': 'You are an experienced recommender systems researcher. Your previous code for research experiment had a bug, so based on the information below, you should revise it in order to fix this bug. Your response should be an implementation outline in natural language, followed by a single markdown code block which implements the bugfix/solution.', 'Research task': " You are an expert recommender systems research assistant who is looking to help the user with their requests.\nThe user has some idea and you want to conduct creative experiments to gain scientific insights.\nYour aim is to run experiments to gather sufficient results to report back to the user.\nThe idea is:\n\nI'd like to run an experiment to quantify how much data split random seeds affect recommender system accuracy. Please use LensKit 0.14.4 to test three algorithms: ALS, ItemKNN, and Pop. Run this on the following three datasets with implicit feedback: MovieLens100K, Amazon Video Games, Last.FM. The raw files are stored in your working directory with the filenames u.data, VideoGames.csv, UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat. First, preprocess all datasets with 5-core filtering. For the Amazon and MovieLens datasets, please also convert any ratings greater than 3 to implicit interactions. Here's the main experimental procedure: Generate 5 different random seeds for data splitting. For each algorithm, dataset, and seed, please do a user-based 80/20 holdout split. Train all models using standard hyperparameters. For the analysis, I need you to measure nDCG@k and Precision@k for k=1, 5, 10 and conduct a short statistical analysis. Please use batch recommendation for all users at once instead of per-user loops for efficiency.", 'Previous (buggy) implementation': '```python\nimport os\nworking_dir = os.path.join(os.getcwd(), \'working\')\nos.makedirs(working_dir, exist_ok=True)\n\nimport warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings(\'ignore\')\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nfrom scipy import stats\n\nfrom lenskit import batch, topn\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.basic import Popular\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.als import ImplicitMF\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.item_knn import ItemItem\n\n# -----------------------------\n# experiment storage\n# -----------------------------\nexperiment_data = {\n    \'ml100k\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': []},\n    \'amazon_vg\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': []},\n    \'lastfm\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': []},\n}\n\nSEEDS = [1, 7, 21, 42, 84]\nKS = [1, 5, 10]\n\n# -----------------------------\n# data loading & preprocessing\n# -----------------------------\ndef load_ml100k(path=\'u.data\'):\n    df = pd.read_csv(path, sep=\'\\t\', header=None, names=[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\', \'timestamp\'])\n    df = df[df[\'rating\'] > 3].copy()\n    return df[[\'user\', \'item\']].assign(rating=1.0)\n\ndef load_amazon_vg(path=\'VideoGames.csv\'):\n    df = pd.read_csv(path)\n    cols = {c.lower(): c for c in df.columns}\n    ucol = cols.get(\'userid\', cols.get(\'user_id\', list(df.columns)[0]))\n    icol = cols.get(\'itemid\', cols.get(\'asin\', cols.get(\'item_id\', list(df.columns)[1])))\n    rcol = cols.get(\'rating\', cols.get(\'overall\', list(df.columns)[2]))\n    df = df[[ucol, icol, rcol]].copy()\n    df.columns = [\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\']\n    df = df[df[\'rating\'] > 3].copy()\n    return df[[\'user\', \'item\']].assign(rating=1.0)\n\ndef load_lastfm(path=\'UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat\'):\n    df = pd.read_csv(path, sep=\'\\t\')\n    cols = {c.lower(): c for c in df.columns}\n    ucol = cols.get(\'userid\', list(df.columns)[0])\n    icol = cols.get(\'artistid\', list(df.columns)[1])\n    df = df[[ucol, icol]].copy().drop_duplicates()\n    df.columns = [\'user\', \'item\']\n    return df.assign(rating=1.0)\n\ndef k_core_filter(df, k=5):\n    cur = df[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\']].drop_duplicates().copy()\n    while True:\n        nu = len(cur)\n        user_counts = cur.groupby(\'user\').size()\n        item_counts = cur.groupby(\'item\').size()\n        cur = cur[cur[\'user\'].isin(user_counts[user_counts >= k].index)]\n        cur = cur[cur[\'item\'].isin(item_counts[item_counts >= k].index)]\n        if len(cur) == nu:\n            break\n    return cur.reset_index(drop=True)\n\ndef user_holdout_split(df, test_ratio=0.2, seed=42):\n    rng = np.random.RandomState(seed)\n    train_parts, test_parts = [], []\n    for _, udf in df.groupby(\'user\', sort=False):\n        n = len(udf)\n        if n < 2:\n            continue\n        n_test = max(1, int(np.ceil(n * test_ratio)))\n        idx = np.arange(n)\n        rng.shuffle(idx)\n        test_idx = idx[:n_test]\n        train_idx = idx[n_test:]\n        if len(train_idx) == 0:\n            train_idx = idx[1:]\n            test_idx = idx[:1]\n        train_parts.append(udf.iloc[train_idx])\n        test_parts.append(udf.iloc[test_idx])\n    train = pd.concat(train_parts, ignore_index=True)\n    test = pd.concat(test_parts, ignore_index=True)\n    common_users = np.intersect1d(train[\'user\'].unique(), test[\'user\'].unique())\n    train = train[train[\'user\'].isin(common_users)].reset_index(drop=True)\n    test = test[test[\'user\'].isin(common_users)].reset_index(drop=True)\n    return train, test\n\n# -----------------------------\n# metrics\n# -----------------------------\ndef dcg_at_k(rels, k):\n    rels = np.asarray(rels)[:k]\n    if rels.size == 0:\n        return 0.0\n    denom = np.log2(np.arange(2, rels.size + 2))\n    return float((rels / denom).sum())\n\ndef evaluate_recs(recs, test, ks=(1,5,10)):\n    truth = test.groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].apply(set).to_dict()\n    recs = recs.sort_values([\'user\', \'rank\'])[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rank\']]\n    rows = []\n    for user, udf in recs.groupby(\'user\', sort=False):\n        gt = truth.get(user, set())\n        items = udf[\'item\'].tolist()\n        hits = [1 if i in gt else 0 for i in items]\n        out = {\'user\': user}\n        for k in ks:\n            hk = hits[:k]\n            out[f\'precision@{k}\'] = float(np.sum(hk) / k)\n            idcg = dcg_at_k(np.ones(min(len(gt), k)), k)\n            out[f\'ndcg@{k}\'] = float(dcg_at_k(hk, k) / idcg) if idcg > 0 else 0.0\n        rows.append(out)\n    return pd.DataFrame(rows)\n\n# -----------------------------\n# model factory\n# -----------------------------\ndef get_algorithms():\n    return {\n        \'ALS\': ImplicitMF(features=50, iterations=15, reg=0.1, weight=40),\n        \'ItemKNN\': ItemItem(30),\n        \'Pop\': Popular(),\n    }\n\n# -----------------------------\n# run experiment\n# -----------------------------\ndatasets = {\n    \'ml100k\': k_core_filter(load_ml100k()),\n    \'amazon_vg\': k_core_filter(load_amazon_vg()),\n    \'lastfm\': k_core_filter(load_lastfm()),\n}\n\nall_results = []\n\nfor dname, df in datasets.items():\n    print(f\'Loaded {dname}: {len(df):,} interactions, {df.user.nunique():,} users, {df.item.nunique():,} items\')\n    for seed in SEEDS:\n        train, test = user_holdout_split(df, test_ratio=0.2, seed=seed)\n        users = np.intersect1d(train[\'user\'].unique(), test[\'user\'].unique())\n        algos = get_algorithms()\n        for aname, algo in algos.items():\n            algo.fit(train)\n            recs = batch.recommend(algo, users, 10)\n            if \'score\' in recs.columns:\n                recs = recs[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rank\', \'score\']]\n            else:\n                recs = recs[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rank\']]\n            ures = evaluate_recs(recs, test, KS)\n            means = ures.drop(columns=[\'user\']).mean().to_dict()\n            row = {\'dataset\': dname, \'algorithm\': aname, \'seed\': seed, **means}\n            all_results.append(row)\n            experiment_data[dname][\'metrics\'][\'val\'].append({\'seed\': seed, \'algorithm\': aname, **means})\n            experiment_data[dname][\'losses\'][\'val\'].append({\'seed\': seed, \'algorithm\': aname, \'validation_loss\': None, \'timestamp\': pd.Timestamp.now().isoformat()})\n            experiment_data[dname][\'predictions\'].append(recs.head(1000).to_dict(\'records\'))\n            experiment_data[dname][\'ground_truth\'].append(test.head(1000).to_dict(\'records\'))\n            print(f\'{dname} | {aname} | seed={seed} | validation_loss = N/A | \' + \', \'.join([f\'{k}={v:.4f}\' for k,v in means.items()]))\n\nresults_df = pd.DataFrame(all_results)\nresults_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, \'seed_sensitivity_results.csv\'), index=False)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, \'experiment_data.npy\'), experiment_data, allow_pickle=True)\nnp.savez_compressed(os.path.join(working_dir, \'results_table.npz\'), results=results_df.to_records(index=False))\n\n# -----------------------------\n# statistical summary\n# -----------------------------\nstats_rows = []\nmetric_cols = [c for c in results_df.columns if \'@\' in c]\nfor (dname, aname), g in results_df.groupby([\'dataset\', \'algorithm\']):\n    for metric in metric_cols:\n        vals = g[metric].values.astype(float)\n        mean = float(np.mean(vals))\n        std = float(np.std(vals, ddof=1)) if len(vals) > 1 else 0.0\n        cv = float(std / mean) if mean != 0 else np.nan\n        try:\n            groups = [results_df[(results_df[\'dataset\'] == dname) & (results_df[\'algorithm\'] == a)][metric].values for a in results_df[results_df[\'dataset\'] == dname][\'algorithm\'].unique()]\n            if len(groups) > 1 and all(len(x) > 1 for x in groups):\n                fstat, pval = stats.f_oneway(*groups)\n            else:\n                fstat, pval = np.nan, np.nan\n        except Exception:\n            fstat, pval = np.nan, np.nan\n        stats_rows.append({\'dataset\': dname, \'algorithm\': aname, \'metric\': metric, \'mean\': mean, \'std\': std, \'cv\': cv, \'anova_F_across_algorithms\': fstat, \'anova_p_across_algorithms\': pval})\n\nstats_df = pd.DataFrame(stats_rows)\nstats_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, \'seed_sensitivity_stats.csv\'), index=False)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, \'seed_sensitivity_stats.npy\'), stats_df.to_dict(\'records\'), allow_pickle=True)\nprint(\'\\nSummary statistics:\')\nprint(stats_df.to_string(index=False))\n\n# -----------------------------\n# visualization\n# -----------------------------\nfor dname in datasets.keys():\n    dres = results_df[results_df[\'dataset\'] == dname].copy()\n    for metric in [\'ndcg@10\', \'precision@10\']:\n        plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))\n        plot_df = [dres[dres[\'algorithm\'] == a][metric].values for a in [\'ALS\', \'ItemKNN\', \'Pop\'] if a in dres[\'algorithm\'].unique()]\n        labels = [a for a in [\'ALS\', \'ItemKNN\', \'Pop\'] if a in dres[\'algorithm\'].unique()]\n        plt.boxplot(plot_df, labels=labels)\n        plt.title(f\'{dname} {metric} across split seeds\')\n        plt.ylabel(metric)\n        plt.tight_layout()\n        fig_path = os.path.join(working_dir, f\'{dname}_{metric.replace("@", "at")}_boxplot.png\')\n        plt.savefig(fig_path, dpi=150)\n        plt.close()\n\nprint(\'\\nPer-seed mean results:\')\nprint(results_df.to_string(index=False))\n```', 'Execution output': '```\nLoaded ml100k: 54,413 interactions, 938 users, 1,008 items\nNumba is using threading layer omp - consider TBB\nfound 1 potential runtime problems - see https://boi.st/lkpy-perf\nconcurrent.futures.process._RemoteTraceback: \n"""\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File "C:\\Users\\Robin\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python311\\Lib\\concurrent\\futures\\process.py", line 261, in _process_worker\n    r = call_item.fn(*call_item.args, **call_item.kwar