[2026/05/08 15:23:35] [DEBUG] isgsa.llm: prompt content: {'Introduction': 'You are an expert recommender systems researcher conducting a code review. Your task is to evaluate whether the code execution was successful or contains bugs. Focus on identifying execution failures, errors, or other issues that would prevent the code from working properly.', 'Research Task': " You are an expert recommender systems research assistant who is looking to help the user with their requests.\nThe user has some idea and you want to conduct creative experiments to gain scientific insights.\nYour aim is to run experiments to gather sufficient results to report back to the user.\nThe idea is:\n\nI'd like to run an experiment to quantify how much data split random seeds affect recommender system accuracy. Please use LensKit 0.14.4 to test three algorithms: ALS, ItemKNN, and Pop. Run this on the following three datasets with implicit feedback: MovieLens100K, Amazon Video Games, Last.FM. The raw files are stored in your working directory with the filenames u.data, VideoGames.csv, UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat. First, preprocess all datasets with 5-core filtering. For the Amazon and MovieLens datasets, please also convert any ratings greater than 3 to implicit interactions. Here's the main experimental procedure: Generate 5 different random seeds for data splitting. For each algorithm, dataset, and seed, please do a user-based 80/20 holdout split. Train all models using standard hyperparameters. For the analysis, I need you to measure nDCG@k and Precision@k for k=1, 5, 10 and conduct a short statistical analysis. Please use batch recommendation for all users at once instead of per-user loops for efficiency.", 'Implementation': '```python\nimport os\nworking_dir = os.path.join(os.getcwd(), \'working\')\nos.makedirs(working_dir, exist_ok=True)\n\nimport time\nimport json\nimport warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings(\'ignore\')\n\nimport inspect\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nfrom scipy import stats\n\nfrom lenskit import batch\nfrom lenskit.algorithms import Recommender\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.basic import Popular\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.als import ImplicitMF\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.item_knn import ItemItem\n\nexperiment_data = {\n    \'ml100k\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': []},\n    \'amazon_vg\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': []},\n    \'lastfm\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': []},\n}\n\nSEEDS = [1, 7, 21, 42, 84]\nKS = [1, 5, 10]\nMAX_K = max(KS)\nDATA_CACHE = os.path.join(working_dir, \'preprocessed_datasets.pkl\')\nSPLIT_CACHE = os.path.join(working_dir, \'splits_cache.pkl\')\n\n\ndef load_ml100k(path=\'u.data\'):\n    df = pd.read_csv(path, sep=\'\\t\', header=None, names=[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\', \'timestamp\'], usecols=[0,1,2])\n    df = df[df[\'rating\'] > 3][[\'user\', \'item\']].drop_duplicates().copy()\n    df[\'rating\'] = 1.0\n    return df[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\']]\n\n\ndef load_amazon_vg(path=\'VideoGames.csv\'):\n    df = pd.read_csv(path)\n    lcols = {c.lower(): c for c in df.columns}\n    ucol = lcols.get(\'userid\', lcols.get(\'user_id\', list(df.columns)[0]))\n    icol = lcols.get(\'asin\', lcols.get(\'itemid\', lcols.get(\'item_id\', list(df.columns)[1])))\n    rcol = lcols.get(\'overall\', lcols.get(\'rating\', list(df.columns)[2]))\n    df = df[[ucol, icol, rcol]].copy()\n    df.columns = [\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\']\n    df = df[df[\'rating\'] > 3][[\'user\', \'item\']].drop_duplicates().copy()\n    df[\'rating\'] = 1.0\n    return df[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\']]\n\n\ndef load_lastfm(path=\'UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat\'):\n    df = pd.read_csv(path, sep=\'\\t\')\n    lcols = {c.lower(): c for c in df.columns}\n    ucol = lcols.get(\'userid\', list(df.columns)[0])\n    icol = lcols.get(\'artistid\', list(df.columns)[1])\n    df = df[[ucol, icol]].drop_duplicates().copy()\n    df.columns = [\'user\', \'item\']\n    df[\'rating\'] = 1.0\n    return df[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\']]\n\n\ndef k_core_filter(df, k=5):\n    cur = df[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\']].drop_duplicates().copy()\n    while True:\n        n0 = len(cur)\n        uc = cur.groupby(\'user\').size()\n        keep_u = uc[uc >= k].index\n        cur = cur[cur[\'user\'].isin(keep_u)]\n        ic = cur.groupby(\'item\').size()\n        keep_i = ic[ic >= k].index\n        cur = cur[cur[\'item\'].isin(keep_i)]\n        if len(cur) == n0:\n            break\n    return cur.reset_index(drop=True)\n\n\ndef user_holdout_split(df, test_ratio=0.2, seed=42):\n    parts_train, parts_test = [], []\n    for _, udf in df.groupby(\'user\', sort=False):\n        n = len(udf)\n        if n < 2:\n            continue\n        udf = udf.sample(frac=1.0, random_state=seed)\n        n_test = max(1, int(np.ceil(n * test_ratio)))\n        if n_test >= n:\n            n_test = 1\n        parts_test.append(udf.iloc[:n_test])\n        parts_train.append(udf.iloc[n_test:])\n    train = pd.concat(parts_train, ignore_index=True)\n    test = pd.concat(parts_test, ignore_index=True)\n    users = np.intersect1d(train[\'user\'].unique(), test[\'user\'].unique())\n    train = train[train[\'user\'].isin(users)].reset_index(drop=True)\n    test = test[test[\'user\'].isin(users)].reset_index(drop=True)\n    return train[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\']], test[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\']]\n\n\ndef dcg_from_hits(hits):\n    if len(hits) == 0:\n        return 0.0\n    idx = np.arange(2, len(hits) + 2)\n    return float((np.asarray(hits, dtype=float) / np.log2(idx)).sum())\n\n\ndef evaluate_recs_fast(recs, test, ks=(1, 5, 10)):\n    truth = test.groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].agg(set).to_dict()\n    rec_lists = recs.sort_values([\'user\', \'rank\']).groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].agg(list).to_dict()\n    users = sorted(truth.keys())\n    rows = []\n    for u in users:\n        gt = truth[u]\n        items = rec_lists.get(u, [])\n        out = {\'user\': u}\n        for k in ks:\n            topk = items[:k]\n            hits = [1.0 if i in gt else 0.0 for i in topk]\n            if len(hits) < k:\n                hits += [0.0] * (k - len(hits))\n            out[f\'precision@{k}\'] = float(np.mean(hits))\n            idcg = dcg_from_hits([1.0] * min(len(gt), k))\n            out[f\'ndcg@{k}\'] = float(dcg_from_hits(hits) / idcg) if idcg > 0 else 0.0\n        rows.append(out)\n    return pd.DataFrame(rows)\n\n\ndef build_recommender(name):\n    if name == \'ALS\':\n        algo = ImplicitMF(features=50, iterations=15, reg=0.1, weight=40)\n    elif name == \'ItemKNN\':\n        algo = ItemItem(30)\n    elif name == \'Pop\':\n        algo = Popular()\n    else:\n        raise ValueError(name)\n    return Recommender.adapt(algo)\n\n\ndef recommend_all(rec_algo, users, n):\n    try:\n        sig = inspect.signature(batch.recommend)\n        if len(sig.parameters) >= 3:\n            recs = batch.recommend(rec_algo, users, n)\n        else:\n            recs = batch.recommend(rec_algo, users)\n    except Exception:\n        recs = batch.recommend(rec_algo, users, n)\n    recs = recs.copy()\n    if \'rank\' not in recs.columns:\n        sort_cols = [\'user\', \'score\'] if \'score\' in recs.columns else [\'user\', \'item\']\n        ascending = [True, False] if \'score\' in recs.columns else [True, True]\n        recs = recs.sort_values(sort_cols, ascending=ascending)\n        recs[\'rank\'] = recs.groupby(\'user\').cumcount() + 1\n    return recs[recs[\'rank\'] <= n].reset_index(drop=True)\n\n\ndef summarize_seed_variation(results_df):\n    rows = []\n    metric_cols = [c for c in results_df.columns if \'@\' in c]\n    for (dname, aname), g in results_df.groupby([\'dataset\', \'algorithm\']):\n        for metric in metric_cols:\n            vals = g.sort_values(\'seed\')[metric].astype(float).to_numpy()\n            mean = float(np.mean(vals))\n            std = float(np.std(vals, ddof=1)) if len(vals) > 1 else 0.0\n            rows.append({\n                \'dataset\': dname, \'algorithm\': aname, \'metric\': metric,\n                \'mean\': mean, \'std\': std,\n                \'cv\': float(std / mean) if mean != 0 else np.nan,\n                \'min\': float(np.min(vals)), \'max\': float(np.max(vals)),\n                \'range\': float(np.max(vals) - np.min(vals))\n            })\n    return pd.DataFrame(rows)\n\n\ndef paired_tests(results_df):\n    out = []\n    metric_cols = [c for c in results_df.columns if \'@\' in c]\n    for dname, ddf in results_df.groupby(\'dataset\'):\n        algs = sorted(ddf[\'algorithm\'].unique())\n        for i in range(len(algs)):\n            for j in range(i + 1, len(algs)):\n                a1, a2 = algs[i], algs[j]\n                g1 = ddf[ddf[\'algorithm\'] == a1].sort_values(\'seed\')\n                g2 = ddf[ddf[\'algorithm\'] == a2].sort_values(\'seed\')\n                merged = g1[[\'seed\'] + metric_cols].merge(g2[[\'seed\'] + metric_cols], on=\'seed\', suffixes=(f\'_{a1}\', f\'_{a2}\'))\n                for metric in metric_cols:\n                    x = merged[f\'{metric}_{a1}\'].to_numpy(dtype=float)\n                    y = merged[f\'{metric}_{a2}\'].to_numpy(dtype=float)\n                    t, p = stats.ttest_rel(x, y) if len(x) > 1 else (np.nan, np.nan)\n                    out.append({\n                        \'dataset\': dname, \'algorithm_1\': a1, \'algorithm_2\': a2,\n                        \'metric\': metric, \'mean_diff\': float(np.mean(x - y)),\n                        \'t_stat\': float(t) if pd.notnull(t) else np.nan,\n                        \'p_value\': float(p) if pd.notnull(p) else np.nan\n                    })\n    return pd.DataFrame(out)\n\n\ndef load_or_prepare_datasets():\n    if os.path.exists(DATA_CACHE):\n        return pd.read_pickle(DATA_CACHE)\n    datasets = {\n        \'ml100k\': k_core_filter(load_ml100k(\'u.data\')),\n        \'amazon_vg\': k_core_filter(load_amazon_vg(\'VideoGames.csv\')),\n        \'lastfm\': k_core_filter(load_lastfm(\'UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat\')),\n    }\n    pd.to_pickle(datasets, DATA_CACHE)\n    return datasets\n\n\ndef load_or_prepare_splits(datasets):\n    if os.path.exists(SPLIT_CACHE):\n        return pd.read_pickle(SPLIT_CACHE)\n    splits = {}\n    for dname, df in datasets.items():\n        splits[dname] = {}\n        for seed in SEEDS:\n            splits[dname][seed] = user_holdout_split(df, test_ratio=0.2, seed=seed)\n    pd.to_pickle(splits, SPLIT_CACHE)\n    return splits\n\n\ndatasets = load_or_prepare_datasets()\nsplits = load_or_prepare_splits(datasets)\nall_results = []\n\nfor dname, df in datasets.items():\n    print(f\'Loaded {dname}: {len(df):,} interactions, {df.user.nunique():,} users, {df.item.nunique():,} items\')\n    for seed in SEEDS:\n        train, test = splits[dname][seed]\n        users = np.intersect1d(train[\'user\'].unique(), test[\'user\'].unique())\n        gt_sample = test.head(1000).to_dict(\'records\')\n        experiment_data[dname][\'ground_truth\'].append({\'timestamp\': pd.Timestamp.now().isoformat(), \'seed\': seed, \'rows\': gt_sample})\n        for aname in [\'ALS\', \'ItemKNN\', \'Pop\']:\n            t0 = time.time()\n            rec_algo = build_recommender(aname)\n            rec_algo.fit(train)\n            recs = recommend_all(rec_algo, users, MAX_K)\n            keep_cols = [c for c in [\'user\', \'item\', \'rank\', \'score\'] if c in recs.columns]\n            recs = recs[keep_cols].copy()\n            ures = evaluate_recs_fast(recs, test, KS)\n            means = ures.drop(columns=[\'user\']).mean().to_dict()\n            val_loss = float(1.0 - means[\'ndcg@10\'])\n            elapsed = time.time() - t0\n            print(f\'Epoch {seed}: validation_loss = {val_loss:.4f}\')\n            print(f\'{dname} | {aname} | seed={seed} | time={elapsed:.1f}s | \' + \', \'.join([f\'{k}={v:.4f}\' for k, v in means.items()]))\n            row = {\'dataset\': dname, \'algorithm\': aname, \'seed\': seed, \'fit_eval_sec\': elapsed, **means}\n            all_results.append(row)\n            ts = pd.Timestamp.now().isoformat()\n            experiment_data[dname][\'metrics\'][\'val\'].append({\'timestamp\': ts, \'seed\': seed, \'algorithm\': aname, **means})\n            experiment_data[dname][\'losses\'][\'val\'].append({\'timestamp\': ts, \'seed\': seed, \'algorithm\': aname, \'validation_loss\': val_loss})\n            experiment_data[dname][\'predictions\'].append({\'timestamp\': ts, \'seed\': seed, \'algorithm\': aname, \'rows\': recs.head(200).to_dict(\'records\')})\n\nresults_df = pd.DataFrame(all_results)\nresults_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, \'seed_sensitivity_results.csv\'), index=False)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, \'experiment_data.npy\'), experiment_data, allow_pickle=True)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, \'seed_sensitivity_results.npy\'), results_df.to_dict(\'records\'), allow_pickle=True)\nnp.savez_compressed(os.path.join(working_dir, \'results_table.npz\'), results=results_df.to_records(index=False))\n\nstats_df = summarize_seed_variation(results_df)\nstats_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, \'seed_sensitivity_stats.csv\'), index=False)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, \'seed_sensitivity_stats.npy\'), stats_df.to_dict(\'records\'), allow_pickle=True)\n\npaired_df = paired_tests(results_df)\npaired_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, \'seed_sensitivity_paired_tests.csv\'), index=False)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, \'seed_sensitivity_paired_tests.npy\'), paired_df.to_dict(\'records\'), allow_pickle=True)\n\nfor dname in datasets.keys():\n    dres = results_df[results_df[\'dataset\'] == dname].copy()\n    for metric in [\'ndcg@10\', \'precision@10\']:\n        plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))\n        data = [dres[dres[\'algorithm\'] == a][metric].values for a in [\'ALS\', \'ItemKNN\', \'Pop\']]\n        plt.boxplot(data, labels=[\'ALS\', \'ItemKNN\', \'Pop\'])\n        plt.title(f\'{dname} {metric} across split seeds\')\n        plt.ylabel(metric)\n        plt.tight_layout()\n        plt.savefig(os.path.join(working_dir, f\'{dname}_{metric.replace("@", "at")}_boxplot.png\'), dpi=150)\n        plt.close()\n\nprint(\'\\nSeed sensitivity summary:\')\nprint(stats_df.to_string(index=False))\nprint(\'\\nPaired t-tests across algorithms using matched seeds:\')\nprint(paired_df.to_string(index=False))\nprint(\'\\nPer-seed mean results:\')\nprint(results_df.to_string(index=False))\n\nwith open(os.path.join(working_dir, \'run_manifest.json\'), \'w\') as f:\n    json.dump({\n        \'seeds\': SEEDS,\n        \'ks\': KS,\n        \'datasets\': {k: {\'n_interactions\': int(len(v)), \'n_users\': int(v.user.nunique()), \'n_items\': int(v.item.nunique())} for k, v in datasets.items()}\n    }, f, indent=2)\n\n```', 'Execution Output': '```\nLoaded ml100k: 54,413 interactions, 938 users, 1,008 items\nNumba is using threading layer omp - consider TBB\nfound 1 potential runtime problems - see https://boi.st/lkpy-perf\nEpoch 1: validation_loss = 0.7901\nml100k | ALS | seed=1 | time=8.6s | precision@1=0.2143, ndcg@1=0.2143, precision@5=0.1765, ndcg@5=0.1993, precision@10=0.1531, ndcg@10=0.2099\nnormalized ratings are zero, centering is not recommended\nEpoch 1: validation_loss = 1.0000\nml100k | ItemKNN | seed=1 | time=8.8s | precision@1=0.0000, ndcg@1=0.0000, precision@5=0.0000, ndcg@5=0.0000, precision@10=0.0000, ndcg@10=0.0000\nEpoch 1: validation_loss = 0.8453\nml100k | Pop | seed=1 | time=2.6s | precision@1=0.2100, ndcg@1=0.2100, precision@5=0.1493, ndcg@5=0.1650, precision@10=0.1205, ndcg@10=0.1547\nEpoch 7: validation_loss = 0.7824\nml100k | ALS | seed=7 | time=3.1s | precision@1=0.2217, ndcg@1=0.2217, precision@5=0.1768, ndcg@5=0.2042, precision