[2026/05/10 10:27:11] [DEBUG] isgsa.backend/openai: [cyan]Raw func call response: Choice(finish_reason='tool_calls', index=0, logprobs=None, message=ChatCompletionMessage(content=None, refusal=None, role='assistant', annotations=[], audio=None, function_call=None, tool_calls=[ChatCompletionMessageFunctionToolCall(id='call_GId9wyP5z9U72l0KsNfbKh9o', function=Function(arguments='{"nl_text":"I will implement a straightforward reproducible baseline around LensKit 0.14.4’s ImplicitMF with ALS on MovieLens 100K from the local u.data file. The script will load the data, apply 5-core filtering on the binarized implicit interactions defined by ratings greater than 3, and then create three 80/20 user-based random holdout splits with distinct seeds. For each split, it will train an ImplicitMF model using LensKit defaults, generate recommendations for all test users in one call with batch.recommend, and evaluate Precision@10 and nDCG@10 against held-out positives. I will aggregate per-user metrics to obtain one score per seed, then compute the mean and standard deviation across seeds. To satisfy the saving requirements, the code will store split-level metrics, per-user metric arrays, and summary statistics both as CSV and as NumPy artifacts in the working directory. Since ALS is not epoch-exposed in LensKit, I will print a simple split-level validation summary after each seed as the suitable interval for tracking evaluation. I will also include a compact visualization of metrics across seeds and save it in the working directory.","code":"import os\\nworking_dir = os.path.join(os.getcwd(), \'working\')\\nos.makedirs(working_dir, exist_ok=True)\\n\\nimport numpy as np\\nimport pandas as pd\\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\nfrom lenskit import batch\\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.als import ImplicitMF\\n\\nexperiment_data = {\\n    \'ml100k_implicit_5core\': {\\n        \'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []},\\n        \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []},\\n        \'predictions\': [],\\n        \'ground_truth\': [],\\n        \'timestamps\': []\\n    }\\n}\\n\\n# Load MovieLens 100K\\ncols = [\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\', \'timestamp\']\\nratings = pd.read_csv(\'u.data\', sep=\'\\\\t\', names=cols, engine=\'python\')\\n\\n# Implicit interactions: rating > 3\\ninter = ratings.loc[ratings[\'rating\'] > 3, [\'user\', \'item\', \'timestamp\']].copy()\\ninter[\'rating\'] = 1.0\\n\\n# 5-core filtering on implicit graph\\nchanged = True\\nwhile changed:\\n    before = len(inter)\\n    ucnt = inter.groupby(\'user\').size()\\n    icnt = inter.groupby(\'item\').size()\\n    inter = inter[inter[\'user\'].isin(ucnt[ucnt >= 5].index) & inter[\'item\'].isin(icnt[icnt >= 5].index)].copy()\\n    changed = len(inter) != before\\n\\ninter = inter[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\']].drop_duplicates().reset_index(drop=True)\\n\\n\\ndef user_holdout(df, seed=0, frac=0.2):\\n    rng = np.random.RandomState(seed)\\n    test_parts = []\\n    train_parts = []\\n    for uid, g in df.groupby(\'user\', sort=False):\\n        idx = g.index.to_numpy()\\n        n = len(idx)\\n        n_test = max(1, int(np.ceil(n * frac)))\\n        test_idx = rng.choice(idx, size=n_test, replace=False)\\n        mask = g.index.isin(test_idx)\\n        test_parts.append(g.loc[mask])\\n        train_parts.append(g.loc[~mask])\\n    train = pd.concat(train_parts, ignore_index=True)\\n    test = pd.concat(test_parts, ignore_index=True)\\n    return train, test\\n\\n\\ndef precision_at_k(rec_items, truth_items, k=10):\\n    if k == 0:\\n        return np.nan\\n    if len(rec_items) == 0:\\n        return 0.0\\n    hits = sum(1 for x in rec_items[:k] if x in truth_items)\\n    return hits / float(k)\\n\\n\\ndef ndcg_at_k(rec_items, truth_items, k=10):\\n    rec = rec_items[:k]\\n    dcg = 0.0\\n    for i, it in enumerate(rec):\\n        if it in truth_items:\\n            dcg += 1.0 / np.log2(i + 2.0)\\n    ideal_len = min(len(truth_items), k)\\n    if ideal_len == 0:\\n        return np.nan\\n    idcg = sum(1.0 / np.log2(i + 2.0) for i in range(ideal_len))\\n    return dcg / idcg if idcg > 0 else 0.0\\n\\n\\nseeds = [1, 2, 3]\\nrows = []\\nall_prec = []\\nall_ndcg = []\\nper_seed_user_metrics = {}\\n\\nfor seed in seeds:\\n    train, test = user_holdout(inter, seed=seed, frac=0.2)\\n\\n    algo = ImplicitMF()  # LensKit 0.14.4 defaults\\n    algo.fit(train[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\']])\\n\\n    test_users = np.sort(test[\'user\'].unique())\\n    recs = batch.recommend(algo, test_users, 10)\\n    if recs is None or len(recs) == 0:\\n        recs = pd.DataFrame(columns=[\'user\', \'item\', \'rank\', \'score\'])\\n\\n    truth = test.groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].apply(set)\\n    rec_groups = recs.groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].apply(list) if len(recs) else pd.Series(dtype=object)\\n\\n    user_rows = []\\n    precs = []\\n    ndcgs = []\\n    for u in test_users:\\n        gt = truth.get(u, set())\\n        rp = rec_groups.get(u, []) if u in rec_groups.index else []\\n        p10 = precision_at_k(rp, gt, 10)\\n        n10 = ndcg_at_k(rp, gt, 10)\\n        precs.append(p10)\\n        ndcgs.append(n10)\\n        user_rows.append((u, p10, n10, len(gt), len(rp)))\\n\\n    mean_p = float(np.nanmean(precs))\\n    mean_n = float(np.nanmean(ndcgs))\\n    all_prec.append(mean_p)\\n    all_ndcg.append(mean_n)\\n    rows.append({\'seed\': seed, \'Precision@10\': mean_p, \'nDCG@10\': mean_n, \'n_test_users\': len(test_users)})\\n    per_seed_user_metrics[f\'seed_{seed}\'] = np.array(user_rows, dtype=object)\\n\\n    experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicit_5core\'][\'metrics\'][\'val\'].append({\\n        \'seed\': seed,\\n        \'Precision@10\': mean_p,\\n        \'nDCG@10\': mean_n,\\n        \'n_test_users\': len(test_users)\\n    })\\n    experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicit_5core\'][\'predictions\'].append(recs[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rank\', \'score\']].to_dict(\'records\'))\\n    experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicit_5core\'][\'ground_truth\'].append(test[[\'user\',