[2026/05/11 11:57:17] [DEBUG] isgsa.backend/openai: [cyan]Raw func call response: Choice(finish_reason='tool_calls', index=0, logprobs=None, message=ChatCompletionMessage(content=None, refusal=None, role='assistant', annotations=[], audio=None, function_call=None, tool_calls=[ChatCompletionMessageFunctionToolCall(id='call_gInpMt3FSUO1QbJDVHvRhjeG', function=Function(arguments='{"nl_text":"I will implement a compact, fully reproducible LensKit 0.14.4 experiment on MovieLens 100K using the local u.data file. The script will load the tab-separated ratings, keep only ratings greater than 3 as implicit positives, and iteratively apply 5-core filtering until all remaining users and items have at least 5 interactions while preserving the original user and item IDs in the data frame. For each of three seeds, it will set both Python and NumPy random seeds, create an independent per-user 80/20 holdout by sampling about 20% of each eligible user’s interactions into test and skipping users that cannot produce both nonempty train and test portions. A fresh LensKit ImplicitMF model with default settings will be trained on each seed’s training split, and top-10 recommendations will be generated for all evaluable users with a single batch recommend call rather than looping over users. The recommendation call will request exclusion of training items so users are not recommended items already seen in training. Evaluation will compute user-level Precision@10 and nDCG@10 from the held-out positives, then average across evaluable users for each seed. The script will save per-seed metrics plus an aggregate mean and standard deviation row to a CSV in the working directory, store experiment artifacts with np.save, and print the aggregate statistics to stdout for quick inspection. I will also keep the code self-contained, concise, and immediately executable at global scope as requested.","code":"import os\\nworking_dir = os.path.join(os.getcwd(), \'working\')\\nos.makedirs(working_dir, exist_ok=True)\\n\\nimport random\\nimport numpy as np\\nimport pandas as pd\\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.als import ImplicitMF\\nfrom lenskit.batch import recommend\\n\\nexperiment_data = {\\n    \'ml100k_implicitmf_repro\': {\\n        \'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []},\\n        \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []},\\n        \'predictions\': [],\\n        \'ground_truth\': [],\\n        \'timestamps\': []\\n    }\\n}\\n\\ndef kcore_implicit(df, min_k=5):\\n    cur = df[[\'user\', \'item\']].drop_duplicates().copy()\\n    while True:\\n        uc = cur.groupby(\'user\').size()\\n        ic = cur.groupby(\'item\').size()\\n        good_u = uc[uc >= min_k].index\\n        good_i = ic[ic >= min_k].index\\n        new = cur[cur[\'user\'].isin(good_u) & cur[\'item\'].isin(good_i)].copy()\\n        if len(new) == len(cur):\\n            return new.reset_index(drop=True)\\n        cur = new\\n\\ndef make_holdout(df, seed, test_frac=0.2):\\n    random.seed(seed)\\n    np.random.seed(seed)\\n    tr_parts, te_parts, eval_users = [], [], []\\n    for u, g in df.groupby(\'user\', sort=False):\\n        n = len(g)\\n        if n < 2:\\n            continue\\n        n_test = max(1, int(round(n * test_frac)))\\n        if n_test >= n:\\n            n_test = n - 1\\n        if n_test <= 0 or n - n_test <= 0:\\n            continue\\n        idx = np.arange(n)\\n        te_idx = np.random.choice(idx, size=n_test, replace=False)\\n        mask = np.zeros(n, dtype=bool)\\n        mask[te_idx] = True\\n        te = g.iloc[mask].copy()\\n        tr = g.iloc[~mask].copy()\\n        if len(te) == 0 or len(tr) == 0:\\n            continue\\n        tr_parts.append(tr)\\n        te_parts.append(te)\\n        eval_users.append(u)\\n    train = pd.concat(tr_parts, ignore_index=True) if tr_parts else df.iloc[0:0].copy()\\n    test = pd.concat(te_parts, ignore_index=True) if te_parts else df.iloc[0:0].copy()\\n    return train, test, np.array(eval_users)\\n\\ndef dcg_at_k(rels, k):\\n    rels = np.asarray(rels)[:k]\\n    if rels.size == 0:\\n        return 0.0\\n    discounts = 1.0 / np.log2(np.arange(2, rels.size + 2))\\n    return float(np.sum(rels * discounts))\\n\\ndef evaluate(recs, test, k=10):\\n    truth = test.groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].apply(set).to_dict()\\n    rows = []\\n    for u, g in recs.groupby(\'user\', sort=False):\\n        pred = g.sort_values(\'rank\')[\'item\'].tolist()[:k]\\n        gt = truth.get(u, set())\\n        if not gt:\\n            continue\\n        hits = np.array([1 if i in gt else 0 for i in pred], dtype=float)\\n        prec = float(hits.sum() / k)\\n        ideal = np.ones(min(len(gt), k), dtype=float)\\n        ndcg = dcg_at_k(hits, k) / dcg_at_k(ideal, k) if ideal.size else 0.0\\n        rows.append((u, prec, ndcg, len(gt)))\\n    m = pd.DataFrame(rows, columns=[\'user\', \'precision\', \'ndcg\', \'n_test\'])\\n    return m\\n\\ncols = [\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\', \'timestamp\']\\nratings = pd.read_csv(\'u.data\', sep=\'\\\\t\', names=cols, engine=\'python\')\\nimplicit = ratings.loc[ratings[\'rating\'] > 3, [\'user\', \'item\']].drop_duplicates().reset_index(drop=True)\\nimplicit = kcore_implicit(implicit, min_k=5)\\nimplicit[\'rating\'] = 1.0\\n\\nseeds = [1, 2, 3]\\nresults = []\\n\\nfor seed in seeds:\\n    train, test, eval_users = make_holdout(implicit[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\']], seed, test_frac=0.2)\\n    test_users = set(test[\'user\'].unique())\\n    train_users = set(train[\'user\'].unique())\\n    eval_users = np.array(sorted(train_users & test_users))\\n    test = test[test[\'user\'].isin(eval_users)].copy()\\n    train = train[train[\'user\'].isin(eval_users)].copy()\\n\\n    model = ImplicitMF()\\n    model.fit(train)\\n    recs = recommend(model, eval_users, 10, candidates=None)\\n\\n    user_train = train.groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].apply(set).to_dict()\\n    recs = recs[~recs.apply(lambda r: r[\'item\'] in user_train.get(r[\'user\'], set()), axis=1)].copy()\\n    recs[\'rank\