[2026/05/11 11:57:51] [DEBUG] isgsa.backend/openai: [cyan]Raw func call response: Choice(finish_reason='tool_calls', index=0, logprobs=None, message=ChatCompletionMessage(content=None, refusal=None, role='assistant', annotations=[], audio=None, function_call=None, tool_calls=[ChatCompletionMessageFunctionToolCall(id='call_inviv9c1HnArrIOGqnM6a6Rh', function=Function(arguments='{"nl_text":"I will implement a compact, fully reproducible LensKit 0.14.4 experiment on MovieLens 100K using the provided u.data file. The script will load the tab-separated ratings, convert ratings > 3 into implicit positives, and iteratively apply 5-core filtering so every retained user and item has at least 5 interactions. For each of three fixed random seeds, it will create an independent per-user 80/20 holdout split, skipping users that cannot support a non-empty train and test partition. A fresh LensKit ImplicitMF model with default settings will be trained on each seed’s training data, and top-10 recommendations will be generated for all evaluable users in a single batch call while excluding training items. The evaluation will compute user-level Precision@10 and nDCG@10, then average them per seed. The script will aggregate the three seeds into mean and standard deviation, save per-seed plus aggregate results to CSV in the working directory, and print the aggregate statistics to stdout. To satisfy reproducibility and artifact requirements, it will also store experiment metadata and metrics with timestamps using NumPy files in the working directory. The implementation stays simple, relies on LensKit where practical, and avoids any hyperparameter tuning so it serves as a clean baseline.","code":"import os\\nworking_dir = os.path.join(os.getcwd(), \'working\')\\nos.makedirs(working_dir, exist_ok=True)\\n\\nimport random\\nimport time\\nimport numpy as np\\nimport pandas as pd\\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.als import ImplicitMF\\nfrom lenskit.batch import recommend\\n\\nexperiment_data = {\\n    \'ml100k_implicitmf_repro\': {\\n        \'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []},\\n        \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []},\\n        \'predictions\': [],\\n        \'ground_truth\': [],\\n        \'timestamps\': [],\\n        \'seeds\': []\\n    }\\n}\\n\\ndef iterative_k_core(df, min_k=5):\\n    cur = df.copy()\\n    while True:\\n        uc = cur.groupby(\'user\').size()\\n        ic = cur.groupby(\'item\').size()\\n        good_users = uc[uc >= min_k].index\\n        good_items = ic[ic >= min_k].index\\n        new_cur = cur[cur[\'user\'].isin(good_users) & cur[\'item\'].isin(good_items)].copy()\\n        if len(new_cur) == len(cur):\\n            return new_cur.reset_index(drop=True)\\n        cur = new_cur\\n\\ndef user_holdout_split(df, test_frac=0.2, seed=0):\\n    rng = np.random.RandomState(seed)\\n    train_parts, test_parts = [], []\\n    eligible_users = []\\n    for user, udf in df.groupby(\'user\', sort=False):\\n        n = len(udf)\\n        n_test = int(np.floor(n * test_frac))\\n        if n < 2 or n_test < 1 or (n - n_test) < 1:\\n            continue\\n        idx = np.arange(n)\\n        rng.shuffle(idx)\\n        test_idx = idx[:n_test]\\n        train_idx = idx[n_test:]\\n        train_parts.append(udf.iloc[train_idx])\\n        test_parts.append(udf.iloc[test_idx])\\n        eligible_users.append(user)\\n    train = pd.concat(train_parts, ignore_index=True) if train_parts else df.iloc[0:0].copy()\\n    test = pd.concat(test_parts, ignore_index=True) if test_parts else df.iloc[0:0].copy()\\n    return train, test, np.array(eligible_users)\\n\\ndef dcg_at_k(rels):\\n    rels = np.asarray(rels, dtype=float)\\n    if rels.size == 0:\\n        return 0.0\\n    denom = np.log2(np.arange(2, rels.size + 2))\\n    return float(np.sum(rels / denom))\\n\\ndef evaluate_topk(recs, test_df, k=10):\\n    truth = test_df.groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].apply(set).to_dict()\\n    precs, ndcgs = [], []\\n    pred_store, gt_store = [], []\\n    for user, udf in recs.groupby(\'user\', sort=False):\\n        rec_items = udf.sort_values(\'rank\')[\'item\'].tolist()[:k]\\n        gt = truth.get(user, set())\\n        if len(gt) == 0:\\n            continue\\n        hits = [1 if it in gt else 0 for it in rec_items]\\n        precs.append(np.sum(hits) / k)\\n        ideal_len = min(k, len(gt))\\n        idcg = dcg_at_k(np.ones(ideal_len))\\n        ndcgs.append(dcg_at_k(hits) / idcg if idcg > 0 else 0.0)\\n        pred_store.append((user, rec_items))\\n        gt_store.append((user, sorted(gt)))\\n    return float(np.mean(ndcgs)), float(np.mean(precs)), pred_store, gt_store\\n\\ncols = [\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\', \'timestamp\']\\nratings = pd.read_csv(\'u.data\', sep=\'\\\\t\', names=cols, engine=\'python\')\\nratings = ratings.loc[ratings[\'rating\'] > 3, [\'user\', \'item\']].copy()\\nratings = ratings.drop_duplicates([\'user\', \'item\']).reset_index(drop=True)\\nratings = iterative_k_core(ratings, min_k=5)\\n\\nseeds = [1, 2, 3]\\nrows = []\\n\\nfor seed in seeds:\\n    np.random.seed(seed)\\n    random.seed(seed)\\n    train, test, eval_users = user_holdout_split(ratings, test_frac=0.2, seed=seed)\\n    if len(train) == 0 or len(test) == 0 or len(eval_users) == 0:\\n        continue\\n\\n    algo = ImplicitMF()\\n    t0 = time.time()\\n    algo.fit(train)\\n    fit_time = time.time() - t0\\n\\n    recs = recommend(algo, pd.Index(eval_users), 10)\\n    ndcg, prec, pred_store, gt_store = evaluate_topk(recs, test, k=10)\\n\\n    ts = time.time()\\n    experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicitmf_repro\'][\'metrics\'][\'val\'].append({\\n        \'seed\': seed, \'ndcg@10\': ndcg, \'precision@10\': prec, \'fit_time_sec\': fit_time, \'timestamp\': ts\\n    })\\n    experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicitmf_repro\'][\'losses\'][\'val\'].append({\\n        \'seed\': seed, \'validation_loss\': float(\'nan\'), \'timestamp\': ts\\n    })\\n    experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicitmf_repro\'][\'predictions\'].append(pred_store)\\n    experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicitmf_repro\'][\'ground_truth\'].append(gt_store)\\n    experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicitmf_repro\'][\'timestamps\'].append(ts)\\n    experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicitmf_repro\'][\'seeds\'].append(seed)\\n\\n    print(f\'Epoch 1: validation_loss = {float(\\"nan\\"):.4f}\')\\n    rows.append({\'seed\': seed, \'ndcg@10\': ndcg, \'precision@10\': prec})\\n\\nres = pd.DataFrame(rows).sort_values(\'seed\').reset_index(drop=True)\\nagg = pd.DataFrame([{\\n    \'seed\': \'mean_std\',\\n    \'ndcg@10\': res[\'ndcg@10\'].mean() if not res.empty else np.nan,\\n    \'precision@10\': res[\'precision@10\'].mean() if not res.empty else np.nan,\\n    \'ndcg@10_std\': res[\'ndcg@10\'].std(ddof=1) if len(res) > 1 else np.nan,\\n    \'precision@10_std\': res[\'precision@10\'].std(ddof=1) if len(res) > 1 else np.nan\\n}])\\n\\nout = res.copy()\\nout[\'ndcg@10_std\'] = np.nan\\nout[\'precision@10_std\'] = np.nan\\nout = pd.concat([out, agg], ignore_index=True)\\nout.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, \'ml100k_lenskit_implicitmf_repro_results.csv\'), index=False)\\n\\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, \'experiment_data.npy\'), experiment_data, allow_pickle=True)\\nnp.savez_compressed(\\n    os.path.join(working_dir, \'ml100k_lenskit_implicitmf_repro_arrays.npz\'),\\n    seeds=np.array(experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicitmf_repro\'][\'seeds\'], dtype=object),\\n    val_metrics=np.array(experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicitmf_repro\'][\'metrics\'][\'val\'], dtype=object),\\n    val_losses=np.array(experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicitmf_repro\'][\'losses\'][\'val\'], dtype=object),\\n    predictions=np.array(experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicitmf_repro\'][\'predictions\'], dtype=object),\\n    ground_truth=np.array(experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicitmf_repro\'][\'ground_truth\'], dtype=object),\\n    timestamps=np.array(experiment_data[\'ml100k_implicitmf_repro\'][\'timestamps\'], dtype=float)\\n)\\n\\nprint(f\\"nDCG@10 mean={agg.iloc[0][\'ndcg@10\']:.6f}, std={agg.iloc[0][\'ndcg@10_std\']:.6f}\\")\\nprint(f\\"Precision@10 mean={agg.iloc[0][\'precision@10\']:.6f}, std={agg.iloc[0][\'precision@10_std\']:.6f}\\")"}', name='return_plan_and_code'), type='function')]))[/cyan]
